What Basque needs
Context
Consistency
Time to connect ideas
Respect for the long arc of meaning
How to communicate with Basque
Anchor your point in the larger pattern
Show how your idea fits into the long thread
Avoid rapid topic‑shifting
Give them space to finish the continuity they’re tracking
What not to do
Don’t demand immediate emotional responses
Don’t interrupt the thread with unrelated details
Don’t treat their long‑view focus as stubbornness
How to support them
Give them continuity.
They will give you stability.
